/-!
# Basics on `SL₂`, its centre, and the image of `PSL₂` in `PGL₂`

This file proves the general facts about `SL₂(F)` and `PSL₂(F)` over a field `F`
needed for Dickson's classification of finite subgroups of `PGL₂(𝔽̄_p)`:

* `SL2.closure_elementary_eq_top`: `SL₂(F)` is generated by the elementary matrices
  `E12 a` and `E21 b`;
* `SL2ToPGL_ker_eq_center` and `SL2_center_card`: the kernel of `SL₂(F) → PGL₂(F)` is
  the centre `{±1}`, of order 2 when `char F ≠ 2`;
* `SL2_card`: `|SL₂(F)| = (q² - 1) * q` for `F` a finite field with `q` elements;
* `PSLImageInPGL_index`: for `F` finite of odd characteristic, the image of `PSL₂(F)`
  in `PGL₂(F)` has index 2, and `index_two_subgroup_iso_PSL`: it is the unique
  subgroup of index two consisting of the classes of matrices with square determinant;
* `PSL2_ZMod3_equiv_GF31`: the identification `PSL₂(𝔽₃) ≃* A₄` obtained by letting
  `SL₂(𝔽₃)` act on the four points of `ℙ¹(𝔽₃)`.
-/

